<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Clarification Request | Quintrin</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Optional clarification to determine review suitability." />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
</head>

<body>

  <header>
    <div class="nav">
      <div class="logo">QUINTRIN</div>
      <nav>
        <a href="/services">Services</a>
        <a href="/intake">Intake</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="container">

    <section>
      <h1>Clarification Request</h1>

      <p>
        To determine whether a structured review is appropriate, we may request
        limited clarification regarding the issue prompting your submission.
      </p>

      <form method="post">
        <label for="issue">
          <strong>Please briefly outline the primary issue you are encountering.</strong>
        </label>

        <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: #5f6b76; margin-top: 0.4rem;">
          Examples may include renewal instability, documentation fragmentation,
          route or regional sensitivity, or underwriter feedback.
        </p>

        <textarea
          id="issue"
          name="issue"
          rows="6"
          style="width: 100%; margin-top: 1rem; padding: 0.75rem; font-family: inherit;"
          placeholder="Brief description..."
        ></textarea>

        <p style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: #5f6b76; margin-top: 1rem; max-width: 600px;">
          This clarification is used solely to assess review suitability.
          Supporting documentation may be requested only if appropriate.
        </p>

        <button class="cta" type="submit" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
          Submit Clarification
        </button>
      </form>
    </section>

  </main>

  <footer>
    <p>
      Quintrin provides independent data structuring services only.
      No insurance placement, underwriting, or claims services are offered.
    </p>
  </footer>

</body>
</html>